+{"id":"frankenjax-4ygi","title":"Cumsum/Cumprod divide by zero on empty selected axis","description":"[HIGH] eval_cumulative in crates/fj-lax/src/reduction.rs computes outer_count = total / axis_dim after axis_dim = tensor.shape.dims[axis] as usize. For a valid empty tensor on the selected axis, e.g. TensorValue::new(DType::I64, Shape { dims: vec![0] }, vec![]), axis_dim == 0 and total == 0, so Primitive::Cumsum/Primitive::Cumprod panic with division by zero. Repro: call eval_primitive(Primitive::Cumsum, &[input], &BTreeMap::new()); the same applies to Cumprod and axis=-1. Expected JAX/NumPy behavior is to return an empty tensor with the same shape/dtype. Add regression tests for shape [0] and a zero-sized selected axis such as [2,0] axis 1, then return early when axis_dim == 0. Note: DB-backed create produced frankenjax-go1z but br sync is currently blocked by stale DB/JSONL divergence, so this JSONL-only bead preserves the finding for implementers.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-29T06:16:28.421936354Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-29T07:01:57.028404709Z","closed_at":"2026-04-29T07:01:57.026610683Z","close_reason":"Returned empty tensors for cumsum/cumprod when the selected axis has length zero","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
